@startuml Admin Operations â€” User Level
title Platform Admin Operations

actor "Platform Admin" as admin
participant "Admin Dashboard" as dash
participant "Organisations" as orgs
participant "Users" as users
participant "Audit Log" as audit
participant "System Health" as sys
participant "Vuln Scanning" as vuln
participant "Vuln Database" as vdb
participant "Test Results" as tests

== Accessing Admin Panel ==

admin -> dash : Navigates to /admin\n(requires platform admin role)
admin -> dash : Sees platform overview:\n- Total orgs, users, products\n- Billing summary\n- System status

== Managing Organisations ==

admin -> orgs : Opens /admin/orgs
admin -> orgs : Sees all organisations\nwith member counts,\nbilling status, product counts
admin -> orgs : Can search by name
admin -> orgs : Clicks into an org to\nview full details

== Managing Users ==

admin -> users : Opens /admin/users
admin -> users : Sees all platform users\nwith email, org, role, status
admin -> users : Can search by email
admin -> users : Can invite new users\nto any organisation

== Viewing Audit Log ==

admin -> audit : Opens /admin/audit-log
admin -> audit : Sees all platform events:\n- Logins, logouts\n- Data changes\n- Admin actions
admin -> audit : Can filter by date,\nuser, or event type

== System Monitoring ==

admin -> sys : Opens /admin/system
admin -> sys : Sees system health:\n- Server status\n- Database connections\n- Scheduler job history
admin -> vuln : Opens /admin/vuln-scan\nto review scan results
admin -> vdb : Opens /admin/vuln-db\nto check database sync status

== Viewing Test Results ==

admin -> tests : Opens /admin/test-results
admin -> tests : Sees Vitest + Playwright\nresults pushed from CI
admin -> tests : Can drill into individual\ntest suites and cases

@enduml
